1
00:02:06,239 --> 00:02:08,960
…The person I thought would take my side

2
00:02:09,960 --> 00:02:11,479
and protect me

3
00:02:12,080 --> 00:02:13,840
turn against me like that.

4
00:02:14,319 --> 00:02:15,560
I'm so sorry.

5
00:02:19,520 --> 00:02:20,639
Mutual understanding

6
00:02:21,240 --> 00:02:23,199
requires an open mind.

7
00:02:23,280 --> 00:02:25,080
When did you get so smart?

8
00:02:25,159 --> 00:02:26,400
Do you like it?

9
00:02:26,479 --> 00:02:27,479
I like it.

10
00:02:30,520 --> 00:02:32,199
What happened to you in the past

11
00:02:32,680 --> 00:02:34,439
made you lose faith in love,

12
00:02:34,520 --> 00:02:38,039
but I'm going to show you
how serious I am about you.

13
00:02:39,879 --> 00:02:41,560
-Mom!
-Mrs. Na.

14
00:02:47,319 --> 00:02:49,840
-Dress up tomorrow.
-Yes?

15
00:02:49,919 --> 00:02:51,479
We are going shopping tomorrow.

16
00:02:52,199 --> 00:02:53,199
Nut.

17
00:02:53,800 --> 00:02:56,319
This is Mr. Nobu.

18
00:02:56,400 --> 00:02:59,080
He wants to buy your show
and broadcast it in Japan.

19
00:03:00,599 --> 00:03:01,520
Hello.

20
00:03:01,599 --> 00:03:02,560
Hello.

21
00:03:05,560 --> 00:03:07,639
-Nice to meet you.
-Nice to meet you, too.

22
00:03:08,120 --> 00:03:10,280
I am from Tokyo. My name is Nobu.

23
00:03:11,000 --> 00:03:12,439
Please be kind to me.

24
00:03:13,080 --> 00:03:15,319
This is Mr. Yoshi.

25
00:03:15,400 --> 00:03:18,159
He is an entertainment reporter.
He's here to interview you.

26
00:03:19,599 --> 00:03:20,479
Nice to meet you.

27
00:03:22,719 --> 00:03:24,439
-Mr. Nobu.
-Yes?

28
00:03:24,520 --> 00:03:27,000
We will go and sign
the contract in my office.

29
00:03:27,680 --> 00:03:31,960
And leave Nut and Mr. Yoshi here
for the interview.

30
00:03:38,599 --> 00:03:40,639
-Mr. Nobu.
-Yes?

31
00:03:40,719 --> 00:03:42,400
Want some Japanese sake?

32
00:03:42,960 --> 00:03:45,240
I love sake.

33
00:03:45,319 --> 00:03:47,800
-Rice whiskey?
-Whiskey.

34
00:04:01,400 --> 00:04:02,719
Mrs. Na,

35
00:04:03,479 --> 00:04:05,319
Nut has not read it yet.

36
00:04:06,159 --> 00:04:07,560
He is probably busy.

37
00:04:09,599 --> 00:04:10,960
That’s all right.

38
00:04:11,039 --> 00:04:12,719
We can go by ourselves.

39
00:04:27,839 --> 00:04:29,160
How about these?

40
00:04:31,639 --> 00:04:33,680
They're a bit bright.

41
00:04:34,439 --> 00:04:36,639
People can see them from miles away.

42
00:04:37,680 --> 00:04:39,680
How about some plain ones?

43
00:04:42,240 --> 00:04:43,680
-Excuse me.
-Yes.

44
00:04:43,759 --> 00:04:45,199
Do you have other colors?

45
00:04:45,759 --> 00:04:47,439
We do. Please wait a moment.

46
00:04:56,839 --> 00:04:57,920
Do they fit well?

47
00:04:59,680 --> 00:05:01,639
They are a little tight.

48
00:05:04,240 --> 00:05:05,519
-Miss.
-Yes?

49
00:05:05,600 --> 00:05:06,920
Do you have a bigger size?

50
00:05:07,000 --> 00:05:08,519
Of course. One moment please.

51
00:05:12,759 --> 00:05:14,600
I will take a look over there.

52
00:05:15,240 --> 00:05:16,240
Okay.

53
00:06:19,800 --> 00:06:21,399
Are they comfy?

54
00:06:35,160 --> 00:06:36,639
Try walking in them.

55
00:07:14,759 --> 00:07:16,120
Anything you like?

56
00:07:17,639 --> 00:07:20,120
They are all pretty. I can't pick one.

57
00:07:22,519 --> 00:07:24,319
Why don't we let Nut pick one for you?

58
00:07:25,279 --> 00:07:26,279
Shall we?

59
00:07:27,240 --> 00:07:28,240
Nut.

60
00:07:28,800 --> 00:07:30,519
Can you pick something for your mom?

61
00:08:18,720 --> 00:08:20,759
I told him

62
00:08:20,839 --> 00:08:22,360
that your phone is broken.

63
00:08:28,680 --> 00:08:29,920
What about this one?

64
00:08:30,519 --> 00:08:31,560
Would it suit Mom?

65
00:08:33,440 --> 00:08:34,679
It looks good.

66
00:08:39,559 --> 00:08:41,879
We should get the right color.

67
00:08:41,960 --> 00:08:43,639
I think she would like a pink one.

68
00:08:51,799 --> 00:08:53,200
Thank you, son.

69
00:09:05,159 --> 00:09:06,360
Let's go.

70
00:09:21,200 --> 00:09:22,600
What color would you like?

71
00:09:24,440 --> 00:09:27,039
The one that best suits my mom.

72
00:09:30,679 --> 00:09:32,879
Then I recommend this shade.

73
00:09:32,960 --> 00:09:33,960
It should suit you.

74
00:09:38,559 --> 00:09:39,720
Do you like it?

75
00:09:40,759 --> 00:09:42,159
How much is it?

76
00:09:42,240 --> 00:09:44,440
It is 599 baht.

77
00:09:47,879 --> 00:09:51,320
I stay home most of the time,
so I don't wear much makeup.

78
00:09:51,799 --> 00:09:53,639
You can look pretty at home too.

79
00:09:56,159 --> 00:09:59,080
Are they both your sons?
They're so handsome.

80
00:10:05,080 --> 00:10:06,080
Yes.

81
00:10:06,840 --> 00:10:08,200
He is my son.

82
00:10:11,360 --> 00:10:12,960
He is also my son.

83
00:10:17,600 --> 00:10:20,120
The three of us are a family.

84
00:10:25,919 --> 00:10:29,759
What about those two? Are they yours too?

85
00:10:29,840 --> 00:10:31,360
They've been looking over here.

86
00:10:33,720 --> 00:10:35,200
Song.

87
00:10:47,879 --> 00:10:49,320
Why are you following me?

88
00:10:50,000 --> 00:10:51,320
Who followed you?

89
00:10:51,399 --> 00:10:53,679
I was passing by and got a little curious.

90
00:10:54,399 --> 00:10:57,679
All this time, I have never seen you
go out with your mother.

91
00:10:57,759 --> 00:10:59,399
So I was wondering

92
00:10:59,480 --> 00:11:02,480
what has gotten into you today.

93
00:11:03,919 --> 00:11:05,399
Nothing much.

94
00:11:05,960 --> 00:11:07,960
I just brought my mom to the mall.

95
00:11:12,039 --> 00:11:15,039
I am glad you are happy.

96
00:11:16,639 --> 00:11:18,080
I've been waiting for this day.

97
00:11:25,879 --> 00:11:27,039
What about you?

98
00:11:28,039 --> 00:11:29,759
Why is he with you?

99
00:11:31,440 --> 00:11:33,600
You and he…

100
00:11:35,440 --> 00:11:36,840
Well, I…

101
00:11:41,240 --> 00:11:42,360
What about us?

102
00:11:42,440 --> 00:11:43,879
Well?

103
00:11:44,960 --> 00:11:45,960
So?

104
00:11:49,200 --> 00:11:50,480
This kid…

105
00:11:52,519 --> 00:11:53,960
is not with me.

106
00:12:02,720 --> 00:12:04,120
It's me…

107
00:12:05,120 --> 00:12:06,320
who is here with him.

108
00:12:09,320 --> 00:12:11,240
So, are you two together?

109
00:12:12,440 --> 00:12:14,799
Yes, as you can see.

110
00:12:16,159 --> 00:12:17,960
You said you didn't like younger guys.

111
00:12:19,480 --> 00:12:20,799
Did I?

112
00:12:20,879 --> 00:12:22,559
When was that? I can't recall.

113
00:12:27,679 --> 00:12:28,919
Well done.

114
00:12:29,480 --> 00:12:32,399
I will reward you with something later.

115
00:12:35,440 --> 00:12:36,720
You are the sweetest.

116
00:12:38,200 --> 00:12:41,360
Why aren’t we ordering something?
I'm hungry.

117
00:12:44,120 --> 00:12:46,399
Go for it, Tofu. Tell me what you want.

118
00:12:46,480 --> 00:12:49,960
Today, I am so happy
that I will treat you.

119
00:12:50,039 --> 00:12:51,960
-You said it.
-Of course.

120
00:12:52,039 --> 00:12:53,080
I'll order, then.

121
00:12:53,159 --> 00:12:54,679
Alright. Go ahead.

122
00:12:54,759 --> 00:12:56,720
-I want this one.
-This one?

123
00:12:56,799 --> 00:12:58,879
-And this.
-And this?

124
00:12:58,960 --> 00:13:00,679
-This one and this one.
-Those two?

125
00:13:00,759 --> 00:13:02,879
This one and this one. I want all of them.

126
00:13:02,960 --> 00:13:04,679
-Good job.
-All… all of them?

127
00:13:04,759 --> 00:13:06,080
Yes.

128
00:13:06,159 --> 00:13:07,399
You want all of them?

129
00:13:07,480 --> 00:13:08,639
Are you sure?

130
00:13:08,720 --> 00:13:10,279
-You said it was a treat.
-Really?

131
00:13:10,360 --> 00:13:11,840
-You said you would pay.
-I will.

132
00:13:11,919 --> 00:13:14,559
Eat what you like and I'll swipe my card.

133
00:13:36,080 --> 00:13:37,799
Hurry up and grow.

134
00:13:37,879 --> 00:13:39,559
There is a kid waiting to eat you.

135
00:13:41,080 --> 00:13:44,240
You're in a good mood today.

136
00:13:44,879 --> 00:13:47,519
You went on a date, right?
I saw Song earlier.

137
00:13:49,960 --> 00:13:52,000
I'm in a good mood because of Nut.

138
00:13:52,080 --> 00:13:56,200
I saw Nut. He took
his mom and Tofu shopping.

139
00:13:56,919 --> 00:13:58,639
Nut made up with his mom.

140
00:13:59,240 --> 00:14:00,440
Really?

141
00:14:03,039 --> 00:14:04,519
A lot of time was wasted though.

142
00:14:07,200 --> 00:14:08,879
What I mean is…

143
00:14:08,960 --> 00:14:13,240
had they reconciled earlier,

144
00:14:13,320 --> 00:14:16,559
they would have spent
much more time together, right?

145
00:14:19,440 --> 00:14:21,159
You too, Gen.

146
00:14:21,240 --> 00:14:23,960
Don’t make love difficult.

147
00:14:24,519 --> 00:14:27,000
You never know what is going to happen.

148
00:14:27,559 --> 00:14:30,840
Be good to each other,
so you don’t regret it later.

149
00:14:33,120 --> 00:14:34,240
You know me.

150
00:14:34,320 --> 00:14:37,679
You are my son after all.
Of course, I know you.

151
00:15:18,279 --> 00:15:19,759
Thank you so much.

152
00:15:20,919 --> 00:15:23,320
I had a great time today, son.

153
00:15:49,120 --> 00:15:52,600
This has made becoming human worthwhile.

154
00:15:53,080 --> 00:15:54,679
At the very least,

155
00:15:54,759 --> 00:15:57,759
I get to help in healing the rift
between Nut and his mom.

156
00:16:22,759 --> 00:16:24,679
It made me realize

157
00:16:25,200 --> 00:16:27,799
that whether you are a mother or a child,

158
00:16:28,279 --> 00:16:30,080
everyone makes mistakes.

159
00:17:05,000 --> 00:17:06,160
I’m going, Mom.

160
00:17:14,119 --> 00:17:15,279
What about…

161
00:17:16,160 --> 00:17:17,200
my lunchbox?

162
00:17:27,359 --> 00:17:28,680
I'm going.

163
00:17:29,240 --> 00:17:30,279
All right.

164
00:17:36,960 --> 00:17:39,799
By accepting each other’s flaws

165
00:17:40,480 --> 00:17:42,759
with love and understanding,

166
00:17:43,799 --> 00:17:45,799
only then can the void be filled.

167
00:17:47,519 --> 00:17:48,599
Seeing this

168
00:17:49,200 --> 00:17:51,119
has been worth it,

169
00:17:53,119 --> 00:17:54,400
even if

170
00:17:55,440 --> 00:17:57,400
I might be gone forever one day.

171
00:18:01,319 --> 00:18:03,160
You're here early, Gen.

172
00:18:03,240 --> 00:18:04,640
You are late.

173
00:18:14,480 --> 00:18:16,920
Hey, Gen. Let go.

174
00:18:18,359 --> 00:18:20,319
You're suddenly so possessive.

175
00:18:21,480 --> 00:18:24,160
-Won't you share anymore?
-No.

176
00:18:25,319 --> 00:18:26,920
It's a good thing Prib isn't here.

177
00:18:27,000 --> 00:18:28,599
Or else she would ask you for some.

178
00:18:29,319 --> 00:18:30,319
You are right.

179
00:18:30,960 --> 00:18:32,519
Where is my niece?

180
00:18:38,279 --> 00:18:40,519
Kuenchai.

181
00:18:41,200 --> 00:18:42,119
Why are you barking?

182
00:18:46,480 --> 00:18:47,519
Prib?

183
00:18:48,079 --> 00:18:49,640
I need to talk to you.

184
00:18:54,440 --> 00:18:56,759
Do you know Tatarn?

185
00:18:57,799 --> 00:18:59,559
Do you know him too?

186
00:19:00,519 --> 00:19:02,079
Did Nut tell you about him?

187
00:19:04,160 --> 00:19:06,400
Nut told me about his ex.

188
00:19:07,079 --> 00:19:08,519
He never told me the name.

189
00:19:09,759 --> 00:19:11,960
I found out his name is Tatarn.

190
00:19:13,359 --> 00:19:15,880
You are friends with him on Facebook.

191
00:19:18,720 --> 00:19:20,759
Can you take me to see him?

192
00:19:21,480 --> 00:19:23,240
I have to ask him something.

193
00:19:23,799 --> 00:19:25,480
I would like to,

194
00:19:26,119 --> 00:19:30,319
but Tarn is in a coma and has not been
responsive for months now.

195
00:19:32,279 --> 00:19:35,000
I really shouldn’t tell you this

196
00:19:35,079 --> 00:19:37,599
as it might be hard for you.

197
00:19:39,079 --> 00:19:41,319
But this is a really important matter.

198
00:19:42,920 --> 00:19:45,200
I want Nut to visit Tarn.

199
00:19:46,079 --> 00:19:48,559
A miracle could happen.

200
00:19:49,440 --> 00:19:50,920
Even if it doesn't,

201
00:19:51,400 --> 00:19:52,640
at least,

202
00:19:53,200 --> 00:19:55,880
Tarn gets to see Nut one last time.

203
00:19:57,519 --> 00:19:59,680
Can you help me just this once?

204
00:20:03,480 --> 00:20:05,640
I've heard people say

205
00:20:06,400 --> 00:20:08,119
that happiness often doesn’t last.

206
00:20:18,039 --> 00:20:20,319
It is actually my secret,

207
00:20:21,359 --> 00:20:23,319
but I will tell you about it.

208
00:20:24,039 --> 00:20:26,279
Before I was into Nut,

209
00:20:26,359 --> 00:20:28,200
I used to like Tarn.

210
00:20:29,319 --> 00:20:31,920
It's a small world sometimes, Tofu.

211
00:20:32,519 --> 00:20:36,480
Two people I liked used to be in love.

212
00:20:37,799 --> 00:20:41,440
And that’s also why I want to help Tarn.

213
00:20:46,319 --> 00:20:49,240
That's why Tarn asked you
to draw him with Nut.

214
00:20:51,359 --> 00:20:55,279
He never mentioned Nut
in that page or on Facebook,

215
00:20:58,119 --> 00:20:59,680
but I can tell

216
00:21:01,279 --> 00:21:03,200
from all those photos and messages

217
00:21:04,200 --> 00:21:05,920
that he wanted Nut to know.

218
00:21:11,400 --> 00:21:13,119
Tarn still loves Nut, doesn't he?

219
00:21:16,160 --> 00:21:18,160
I don’t know about that.

220
00:21:18,640 --> 00:21:20,759
All I know is that

221
00:21:20,839 --> 00:21:23,519
Tarn never wanted to trouble Nut.

222
00:21:24,039 --> 00:21:27,400
Tarn told me
that he wanted Nut to be happy.

223
00:21:27,480 --> 00:21:29,519
He wants him to do the job he loves

224
00:21:29,599 --> 00:21:31,839
and be surrounded by good people.

225
00:21:32,720 --> 00:21:34,519
And what happened between them

226
00:21:35,039 --> 00:21:39,039
should just be left as a happy memory.

227
00:21:41,400 --> 00:21:44,119
Isn’t that obvious?

228
00:21:47,640 --> 00:21:49,400
If he is still in love with Nut,

229
00:21:50,759 --> 00:21:52,799
why didn’t he come back for him?

230
00:21:54,559 --> 00:21:55,880
I know why.

231
00:21:59,039 --> 00:22:00,279
What did you just say?

232
00:22:00,799 --> 00:22:01,799
Well,

233
00:22:02,599 --> 00:22:04,319
you were wondering

234
00:22:04,400 --> 00:22:06,160
why they didn’t get back together.

235
00:22:08,519 --> 00:22:12,880
I think the guy is not sure
if the girl wants him back.

236
00:22:13,720 --> 00:22:15,359
Though they used to love each other

237
00:22:15,839 --> 00:22:17,480
and they broke up out of necessity,

238
00:22:18,400 --> 00:22:20,400
no one stays the same forever.

239
00:22:21,319 --> 00:22:23,680
Now that the girl has feelings
for that other guy,

240
00:22:24,480 --> 00:22:26,799
the guy who has been waiting

241
00:22:26,880 --> 00:22:28,000
is now afraid to act.

242
00:22:32,960 --> 00:22:34,039
Well…

243
00:22:35,079 --> 00:22:37,480
How do you think it will end?

244
00:22:38,839 --> 00:22:40,160
Just wait and see.

